{
  "text": "A recent published study showed a prolonged TTT in several patients and erroneous absence of VF detection during induced arrhythmias at the time of DFT testing due to noise in 5 patients. All 5 patients were programmed in the primary sensing vector. Data on the position of the S-ICD system were inconclusive. [CITATION_1] In consonance with this previous article, in this case we describe a similar sensing issue leading to inhibition of shock therapy during DFT following elective S-ICD replacement. Within our tertiary center with 10 years of S-ICD experience, 375 de novo S-ICD implants and 140 S-ICD box changes, this was the first and only observed case of noise during DFT with subsequent inhibition of shock therapy. We argue that this sensing issue during DFT only occurs in rare cases.",
